br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   another question</span><hr size=1> recently, one of UC's clerics who was on military duty has returned from a long leave of abscence.  she is basically ready to join the list (and has been since before the list existed, but was on military leave).  so she should be on it soon.  but i was wondering, is it permissable for 2 clerics who mutual agree to swap spots on the list?  i know we are really trying to keep this on an individual as opposed to guild level, but i know the clerics in UC might want to shift around the list to accomodate this cleric who was ready earlier, but wasn't around to get onto the list when it formed.  <br>
<br>
i'd love to hear some cleric perspective on this  /shrug  its your show, i'm just curious about the details. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/umedicca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Medicca</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>1st post by this guy</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/2/02 12:12:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: another question</span><hr size=1> I think it is ok for members within the same guild or who are friends to swap spots..sure... But just getting on the list because of RL commitments isn't quite fair.  We all have RL committments, granted some take longer then others, but still this is a game and since this list has been created the person that was away from the game--gets added when they email all the requirements to Saela <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/umedicca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Medicca</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/2/02 12:12:57 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uracknarsteelhammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Racknar Steelhammer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Lubba</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/2/02 12:22:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: another question</span><hr size=1> As long as both Clerics are already on the list and the swapping affects no other Clerics placement then sure why not.  Just as long as everyone agrees to it and Saela is kept well informed of it I see no problem. <p><p>Racknar Steelhammer<br>58 Templar of Brell <br>Guardians of the Keep <br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=140143>Character Profile</a><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=257064>Klarisa's Profile</a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/useke2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>seke2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#3333cc>Drinalese</font></span><br>  Posts: 398<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/2/02 12:59:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: another question</span><hr size=1> yeah, i'm not saying &quot;oh poor cleric was out of eq, they should get the 1st spot!&quot;<br>
<br>
what i'm saying is, hey, would it be a problem if a few clerics &quot;juggled&quot; their spots?  regardless of guildtag or whatever.  nobody would be impacted except the clerics who were involved in the swaps.  i mean, the cleric who is coming back to eq from military duty is joining the list either way.  the question is just, would it be permissable for clerics to swap spots with eachother.  not bumping or moving anyone, just 2 people changing positions.<br>
<br>
wanted to know if i should even bother investigating this as a possibility. <br>
<br>
thanks  =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/usaelavee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saela Vee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Priestess of The Kindred</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/3/02 8:20:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: another question</span><hr size=1> Please refer to Rule No. 1. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uraytheonhcn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RaytheonHCN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=red><B>Dranalite<B></FONT></span><br>  Posts: 170<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/3/02 10:42:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.highcouncil.net/panani1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: another question</span><hr size=1> Rule 1 doesn't exactly apply.  He's not asking for the ability for his guild to substitute one cleric for another when ragefire pops, he is asking can any 2 clerics, regardless of guild, exchange places on the list.  I don't see where anyone at all could have a problem with this as long as the swap does not involve the cleric that is currently in the top spot camping rage.  The only abuse I could possibly forsee is some cleric who has no intention of completing his/her epic brokering away his/her spot on the list every time he/she gets near the top.  That situation should be easy enough to identify and deal with. <p><center>
