<br>
Signing up for the RF list means you are ready to take your place on the list.  Any circumstances or situations that may occur where the first two or three clerics are not prepared for their turn/camp can be handled at that time, based on the facts of that particular situation.<br>
<br>
I could name hypothetic situations a mile wide, but it does no good to address them unless or until they actually occur.<br>
<br>
Is there a particular situation, Seke, where one of your guild's clerics is not prepared for his or her RF camp? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uraytheonhcn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RaytheonHCN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=red><B>Dranalite<B></FONT></span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/3/02 6:25:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.highcouncil.net/panani1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: another question</span><hr size=1> What does the reason matter?  If both clerics agree to the swap, it does not affect anyone else on the list.  No one else will get their chance any sooner or later, except the clerics that agree on the swap.  What negative consequences do you forsee?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uraytheonhcn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RaytheonHCN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=red><B>Dranalite<B></FONT></span><br>  Posts: 174<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/3/02 6:37:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.highcouncil.net/panani1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: another question</span><hr size=1> Besides, the 2 clerics involved could just trade MQ's of the Orb of Vapor after each kills Rage, and most people would never know.  <br>
<br>
(except for the 2nd cleric having an epic at his own rage kill :p) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uraytheonhcn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RaytheonHCN</A> at: 7/3/02 6:47:16 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/unirtox.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nirtox</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Emrok's Daddy</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/4/02 12:03:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: another question</span><hr size=1> HiHo<br>
